Here's the approach:

## 1. Define theme ResourceDictionaries

Create a separate XAML `ResourceDictionary` for each theme:

```xml
<!-- Themes/LightTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="PrimaryText">#1A1A1A</Color>
    <Color x:Key="Accent">#0078D4</Color>
    <!-- ... -->
</ResourceDictionary>
```

Repeat for `DarkTheme.xaml` and `HighContrastTheme.xaml` with the same keys but different values.

## 2. Apply keys in your styles/pages

```xml
<Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryText}" />
<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource PageBackground}" />
```

Use **`DynamicResource`** (not `StaticResource`) so values update at runtime.

## 3. Create a theme service

```csharp
public static class ThemeService
{
    public static void ApplyTheme(string themeName)
    {
        var mergedDictionaries = Application.Current!.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
        mergedDictionaries.Clear();

        var theme = themeName switch
        {
            "Dark"         => new DarkTheme(),
            "HighContrast"  => new HighContrastTheme(),
            _               => new LightTheme(),
        };

        mergedDictionaries.Add(theme);

        // Persist the choice
        Preferences.Set("AppTheme", themeName);
    }
}
```

## 4. Wire up the settings page

```xml
<Picker x:Name="ThemePicker" Title="Theme"
        SelectedIndexChanged="OnThemeChanged">
    <Picker.ItemsSource>
        <x:Array Type="{x:Type x:String}">
            <x:String>Light</x:String>
            <x:String>Dark</x:String>
            <x:String>HighContrast</x:String>
        </x:Array>
    </Picker.ItemsSource>
</Picker>
```

```csharp
void OnThemeChanged(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    if (ThemePicker.SelectedItem is string theme)
        ThemeService.ApplyTheme(theme);
}
```

## 5. Restore on startup

In `App.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(Preferences.Get("AppTheme", "Light"));
}
```

**Key points:**
- **`DynamicResource` everywhere** — this is what makes live switching work.
- **Same keys across all three dictionaries** — swap the dictionary, every bound property updates.
- **`Preferences`** persists the user's choice across launches.
